---
name: curried-extern-import
backends: [int]
---

# A curried block-form extern is importable by name

Regression for `v2-httpclient-curried-extern-unbound`: `httpClient(base){ block }`
is an eval-time special form (`EvalRuntime.reservedApplyHeads`), not a plugin
native, so the v1 interpreter left it unbound and it never landed in
`exportedGlobals`. That made `import [httpClient](http.ssc)` fail name resolution
*at import time* ("'httpClient' not found in …"), even though the call itself works.
StatRuntime now registers a placeholder global for such block-form externs so the
import resolves; the call always takes the special-form path, never the placeholder.

[httpClient, httpTimeout, httpRetry](../../v1/runtime/std/http.ssc)

```scalascript
def main(): Unit =
  println("imported ok")
```
